# Odoo Security Rules

## ACLs

- Every new persistent model needs an `ir.model.access.csv` entry unless it is intentionally internal and inaccessible.
- ACLs must be least-privilege: separate read/write/create/unlink by group.
- Transient models used by wizards need appropriate access for the groups that launch them.

## Record Rules and Groups

- Use record rules when users should see only a subset of records.
- Confirm multi-company behavior for company-dependent models.
- Use existing Odoo groups where possible; create new groups only for a real permission boundary.
- Menu groups, view groups, ACL groups, and record rule groups must be consistent.

## Public and Portal Exposure

- Public controllers and portal methods must validate tokens, ownership, company, website, and record access.
- Do not expose unrestricted searches, record IDs, or binary fields to public users.
- Methods callable through RPC must not rely on client-side checks.

## Sudo and Raw SQL

- `sudo()` requires a local comment explaining why bypassing access rules is safe.
- Raw SQL must be parameterized and must not bypass record rules for user-facing data unless explicitly controlled.

## Deliverables

- Any new model feature must include security review notes.
- Missing ACLs, overly broad ACLs, or missing record rules block production readiness.
